        "beatType": "motion_graphics",
        "startFrame": 1275,
        "endFrame": 1992,
        "componentPath": "src/visuals/Generated_DopamineRedBadge.tsx",
        "transcriptSegment": "When a notification arrives, your brain releases a small hit of dopamine. Not because of the content, but because of the anticipation. The red badge on your app icon is doing the same thing. It creates an open loop in your mind, an unresolved tension that can only be closed by tapping it. This is called the Zeigarnik effect. Your brain obsesses over incomplete tasks.",
